随着二战后期[[纳粹德国|纳粹德国]]占领军的撤退和[[苏联红军|苏联红军]]的胜利抵达，'''中欧和东欧的反犹太人暴力'''部分归咎于战后社会动荡和经济混乱——这动荡和混乱由于在扩张后的苏联[[加盟共和国|加盟共和国]]全部领土及新的卫星国全面强制实施的[[斯大林主义|斯大林主义]]政策而进一步恶化。在饱受战争蹂躏的苏联城镇里，在市场、物资耗尽的商场、学校，甚至国有企业里，反犹攻击频频发生。<ref name="W-H-S">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?redir_esc=y&id=iO1u1qjs61IC&q=anti-semitic%2Bincidents|title=War, Holocaust and Stalinism: A Documented Study of the Jewish Anti-Fascist Committee in the USSR|last=Shimon Redlich, Kirill Mikhaĭlovich Anderson, I. Alʹtman|publisher=Psychology Press|year=1995|pages=38-44, 97, 229, 459|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2020-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306083432/https://books.google.com/books?redir_esc=y&id=iO1u1qjs61IC&q=anti-semitic+incidents|dead-url=no}}</ref>抗议信从数不清的[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]]、[[乌克兰|乌克兰]]和[[白俄罗斯|白俄罗斯]]城镇发往[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]，这些信是对犹太人大屠杀进行记录的[[犹太人反法西斯委员会|犹太人反法西斯委员会]]发出的。<ref name="W-H-S" />

== 历史 ==
如大卫·德拉贡斯基（Colonel David Dragunsky）所写的，苏联当局未能解决[[希特勒|希特勒]]多年的反犹宣传；[[苏联从前的纳粹合作者|苏联从前的纳粹合作者]]常常被委派负责国有企业。<ref name="W-H-S" />[[所罗门·米哈伊洛维奇·米霍埃尔斯|所罗门·米哈伊洛维奇·米霍埃尔斯]]（JAFC主席，1948年1月在明斯克被谋杀）曾写道：犹太人的家园没有得到返还。在[[別爾基切夫|别尔基切夫]]、[[莫吉利夫-波季利西基|莫吉利夫-波季利西基]]、[[巴爾塔|巴爾塔]]、[[日梅林卡|日梅林卡]]、[[文尼察|文尼察]]、[[赫梅利尼克|赫梅利尼克]]、[[舊拉法利夫卡|舊拉法利夫卡]]和许多其它城镇，犹太人为了自身安全，被迫滞留在纳粹时期的[[犹太人隔离区|犹太人隔离区]]。<ref name="W-H-S" />在20世纪40年代后期所谓的“[[无根世界主义者|无根世界主义者]]”运动中，以及在“[[被谋杀的诗人之夜|被谋杀的诗人之夜]]”事件中，[[犹太人反法西斯委员会|犹太人反法西斯委员会]]（JAFC）成为苏联当局直接指斥的对象。<ref name="Medvedev">{{Cite book|url=http://scepsis.net/library/id_1473.html|title=Сталин и еврейская проблема: новый анализ|last=Medvedev|first=Zhores|authorlink=Zhores Medvedev|publisher=Prava Cheloveka|year=2003|isbn=5-7712-0251-7|location=Moscow|page=148|trans-title=Stalin and the Jewish Question: New Analysis|ref=harv|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028123719/https://scepsis.net/library/id_1473.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Pinkus">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=V7g8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA183#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Soviet Government and the Jews 1948-1967: A Documented Study|last=Pinkus|first=Benjamin|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1984|isbn=0-521-24713-6|location=Cambridge|pages=183–184|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2019-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903145328/https://books.google.com/books?id=V7g8AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA183#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{Quote|JAFC主席团于1944年8月下旬会见了一位从白俄罗斯来的犹太党派的领导人。在回答关于[[明斯克|明斯克]]的非犹太人对犹太人的态度问题时，他陈述：“…态度相当不好。已经发生了很多次反犹太人的事件…已经开始争抢公寓…还有很多就业方面的困难。”<ref name="W-H-S"/>}}

米霍埃尔斯被刺杀后数月内，多名其他犹太知名人士遭逮捕。他的死亡标示着在全国范围内镇压犹太人的开始——指控他们从事间谍活动和经济犯罪行为。1948年秋天爆发了一场反[[锡安主义|锡安主义]]运动。40年代末，犹太人从苏联加盟共和国执政党的上层消失了。<ref name="ZYGi">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=crBhRHqSlJYC&q=Mikhoels+murder|title=The Black Years and the Gray, 1948-1967|last=Zvi Y. Gitelman|work=A Century of Ambivalence: The Jews of Russia and the Soviet Union, 1881 to the Present|publisher=Indiana University Press|year=2001|pages=144-154}}</ref>此后不久，在1952-53年发生了[[犹太医生杀手案|犹太医生杀手案]]，继而在媒体上出现反犹太主义宣传，<ref name="Brent-Naumov">{{Cite book|title=Stalin's Last Crime: The Plot Against the Jewish Doctors, 1948-1953|url=https://archive.org/details/stalinslastcrime0000bren|last=Brent|first=Jonathan|last2=Vladimir P. Naumov|publisher=HarperCollins|year=2003|isbn=0-06-019524-X|location=New York|page=[https://archive.org/details/stalinslastcrime0000bren/page/4 4]}}</ref>及数百起酷刑审讯事件。<ref name="S-Mo">{{Cite book|title=Stalin: The Court of the Red Tsar|url=https://archive.org/details/stalincourtofred0000seba_s9j1|last=Sebag-Montefiore|first=Simon|authorlink=Simon Sebag-Montefiore|publisher=Vintage Books|year=2005|isbn=1-4000-7678-1|location=New York|page=[https://archive.org/details/stalincourtofred0000seba_s9j1/page/636 636]}}</ref>苏联绝大部分社会团体从不承认当地辅警参与过[[犹太人大屠杀|犹太人大屠杀]]。<ref name="MM">{{Cite journal|title=Auxiliary Police Units in the Occupied Soviet Union, 1941-43: A Case Study of the Holocaust in Gomel, Belarus|author=Meredith M. Meehan|url=https://www.usna.edu/History/_files/documents/Honors-Program/2010/Meehan_Honors_Thesis.pdf|publisher=United States Naval Academy|year=2010|page=44|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2016-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606073313/http://www.usna.edu/History/_files/documents/Honors-Program/2010/Meehan_Honors_Thesis.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="AG">{{Cite journal|title=Memorial Narratives of WWII Partisans and Genocide in Belarus|author=Alexandra Goujon|url=http://ww2-historicalmemory.org.ua/docs/eng/Goujon.doc|date=2008-08-28|publisher=University of Bourgogne|location=France|page=4|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805231205/http://ww2-historicalmemory.org.ua/docs/eng/Goujon.doc|archivedate=2016-08-05|access-date=2017-02-26}}</ref><ref name="JPHi">{{Cite journal|title=Bringing the Dark Past to Light. The Reception of the Holocaust in Postcommunist Europe|url=http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/Supplements/excerpts/Spring%2013/9780803225442_excerpt.pdf|last=John-Paul Himka and Joanna Beata Michlic|publisher=University of Nebraska Press|page=16|isbn=0803246471|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022072804/http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/Supplements/excerpts/Spring%2013/9780803225442_excerpt.pdf|archivedate=2015-10-22|journal=|access-date=2017-02-26}}</ref> 苏联的德占区的30万名[[辅警|辅警]]绝大部分平静地回归了战前的生活，包括“[[白俄罗斯保卫家园|白俄罗斯保卫家园]]”组织的成员。<ref name="dean">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tdzTU1Uj3zcC&pg=PA60|title=Collaboration in the Holocaust: Crimes of the Local Police in Belorussia and Ukraine, 1941-44|last=Dean|first=Martin|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|year=2003|isbn=9781403963710|page=60|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2019-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190902183745/https://books.google.com/books?id=tdzTU1Uj3zcC&pg=PA60|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ASi-1">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u21Wsx6PtMUC&q=%28Schutzmannschaft%29|title=Bashert: A Granddaughter's Holocaust Quest|last=Andrea Simon|work=Atonement|publisher=Univ. Press of Mississippi|year=2002|isbn=1578064813|page=225|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2020-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802213756/https://books.google.com/books?id=u21Wsx6PtMUC&q=%28Schutzmannschaft%29|dead-url=no}}</ref>该组织参与过镇压行动，其中3万多犹太人被杀。 <ref name="Mironowicz">{{Cite web|url=http://autary.iig.pl/mironowicz_e/knihi07-26.htm|title=Okupacja niemiecka na Białorusi|accessdate=2014-07-12|author=Eugeniusz Mironowicz|year=2014|work=Historia Białorusi od połowy XVIII do XX w. [History of Belarus, mid 18th century until the 20th century]|publisher=Związek Białoruski w RP, Katedra Kultury Białoruskiej  Uniwersytetu w Białymstoku (Internet Archive)|language=pl, be|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927221149/http://autary.iig.pl/mironowicz_e/knihi07-26.htm|archivedate=2007-09-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref>此外还有“[[乌克兰警卫营|乌克兰警卫营]]”成员，该组织仅在[[沃利尼亚|沃利尼亚]]一地就屠杀了15万犹太人。<ref name="ASt">{{Cite book|title=The Soviet Counterinsurgency in the Western Borderlands|url=https://archive.org/details/sovietcounterins00stat|last=Alexander Statiev|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2010|page=[https://archive.org/details/sovietcounterins00stat/page/n85 69]}}</ref>[[赫鲁晓夫|赫鲁晓夫]]曾宣布，犹太人在乌克兰不受欢迎。<ref name="BPi">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=52Ew77pZsNUC&q=proclaimed+not+welcome|title=The Jews of the Soviet Union: The History of a National Minority|last=Benjamin Pinkus|work=Anti-Semitism|isbn=0521389267|page=219}}</ref>

== 卫星国 ==
由于苏联占领了[[波兰|波兰]]，“（犹太人）的死亡只有一小部分可以归因于反犹太主义。”[[扬•格罗斯|扬•格罗斯]]写道。<ref name="Gross">{{Cite book|title=Studies in Contemporary Jewry|last=Gross|first=Jan T.|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2005|isbn=0-19-518224-3|editor-last=Jonathan Frankel|chapter=After Auschwitz: The Reality and Meaning of Postwar Antisemitism in Poland}}</ref>大多数人的死亡都是由于反对新的亲苏政府而发起的[[反共产主义暴乱|反共产主义暴乱]]导致的。<ref name="SG-1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ceeol.com/aspx/getdocument.aspx?logid=5&id=21F8A4F9-9306-4E36-81FD-7E84C781B737|title=Central and Eastern European Online Library (CEEOL); page 11, note 7 of current document|author=August Grabski|format=PDF|work=Book review of Stefan Grajek, "Po wojnie i co dalej? Żydzi w Polsce, w latach 1945−1949", translated from Hebrew by Aleksander Klugman, [[Żydowski_Instytut_Historyczny|Żydowski Instytut Historyczny]], Warsaw 2003 (p. 95)|publisher=Kwartalnik Historii Żydów, Recenzje (Jewish History Quarterly; Reviews)|language=pl|accessdate=2017-02-26|archive-date=2012-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120729232906/http://www.ceeol.com/aspx/getdocument.aspx?logid=5|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[1944-46年在波兰发生的反犹暴力活动|1944-46年在波兰发生的反犹暴力活动]]夺走了至少327名犹太人的生命。<ref name="Engel">{{Cite book|title=Yad Vashem Studies Vol. XXVI|last=Engel|first=David|publisher=[[Yad_Vashem|Yad Vashem]]|year=1998|page=32|chapter=Patterns Of Anti-Jewish Violence In Poland, 1944-1946|chapterurl=http://www1.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%203128.pdf|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2019-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204194618/https://www.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft|dead-url=no}}</ref>

数百名返回[[罗马尼亚|罗马尼亚]]的犹太人丧生。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jcpa.org/JCPA/Templates/ShowPage.asp?DRIT=3&DBID=1&LNGID=1&TMID=111&FID=624&PID=0&IID=2329&TTL=Manfred_Gerstenfeld_on_The_Jews_Are_Coming_Back:_The_Return_of_the_Jews_to_Their_Countries_of_Origin_after_WWII|title=Institute for Global Jewish Affairs – Global Antisemitism, Anti-Israelism, Jewish Studies|accessdate=2010-04-08|author=Minicy Catom Software Engineering Ltd. www.catom.com|date=1946-07-04|publisher=Jcpa.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100613080315/http://jcpa.org/JCPA/Templates/ShowPage.asp?DRIT=3&DBID=1&LNGID=1&TMID=111&FID=624&PID=0&IID=2329&TTL=Manfred_Gerstenfeld_on_The_Jews_Are_Coming_Back:_The_Return_of_the_Jews_to_Their_Countries_of_Origin_after_WWII|archive-date=2010-06-13|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>[//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Ancel Jean Ancel], "The Return of the Survivors from Transnistria," in David Bankier, ed., The Jews Are Coming Back (Yad Vashem, 2005), 241.</ref>在[[匈牙利|匈牙利]]也多处爆发了反犹太人的示威，甚至流血冲突事件，<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Tdn6FFZklkcC&pg=RA1-PA333&lpg=RA1-PA333&dq=hungary+pogroms&source=web&ots=qJXqqbyIWO&sig=aXHp-luRrNeDV7WWrPEs_5kkO78&hl=pl&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=1&ct=result|title=Antisemitism: a historical ... - Google Książki|date=1939-01-30|publisher=Books.google.pl|accessdate=2010-04-08|archive-date=2019-08-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827173019/https://books.google.com/books?id=Tdn6FFZklkcC&pg=RA1-PA333&lpg=RA1-PA333&dq=hungary+pogroms&source=web&ots=qJXqqbyIWO&sig=aXHp-luRrNeDV7WWrPEs_5kkO78&hl=pl&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=1&ct=result|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.polhist.hu/multunk/letoltes/petoa.pdf|title=Népbiróság és vérvád az 1945 utáni Budapesten|accessdate=2010-04-08|author=Petö Andrea|format=PDF|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721112348/http://www.polhist.hu/multunk/letoltes/petoa.pdf|archivedate=2011-07-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0411/is_/ai_76026452|title=Antisemitism in Post World War II Hungary - violence, riots; Communist Party policy | Judaism | Find Articles at BNET|last=Kenez|first=Peter|publisher=Findarticles.com|accessdate=2010-04-08|year=2001|archive-date=2012-07-11|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120711024459/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0411/is_2_50/ai_76026452/|dead-url=no}}</ref>例如在[[孔毛道劳什|孔毛道劳什]]（2人或4人被害）及[[米什科尔茨|米什科尔茨]]。

1945年9月，在[[斯洛伐克|斯洛伐克]]的[[托波爾恰尼|托波爾恰尼]]，48名犹太人受到严重伤害。12月，多名犹太人在[[科尔巴索夫|科尔巴索夫]]被杀。1946年8月1-5日，发生13起反犹事件，被报道为党派大屠杀，其中最大的一起在[[日利納|日利納]]，其中有15人受伤。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cs-magazin.com/index.php?a=a2006081058|title=CS Magazin|accessdate=2010-04-08|publisher=CS Magazin|archive-date=2020-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220095520/http://www.cs-magazin.com/index.php?a=a2006081058|dead-url=no}}</ref>1946年8月和1948年8月，在[[伯拉第斯拉瓦|伯拉第斯拉瓦]]发生反犹示威，同时其它很多地方也爆发了反犹太人的骚乱。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Protizidovske vytrznosti v Bratislave v historicksom kontexte|author=Mgr. Ivica Bumova, PhD|url=http://www.upn.gov.sk/publikacie_web/pamat-naroda/pamat-naroda-03-2007.pdf|publisher=Studie Pamat Naroda|at=28 (27 / 100) in PDF|quote=The Jewish demands to return lost property caused and open resistance of a certain part of Slovak community. The frustration was transformed into anti-Jewish riots that took place in Bratislava and several other cities and villages...|access-date=2017-02-26|archive-date=2013-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006053652/http://www.upn.gov.sk/publikacie_web/pamat-naroda/pamat-naroda-03-2007.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.druhasvetova.sk/2013/06/17/protizidovske-nepokoje-v-bratislave-august-1946-august-1948-v-atmosfere-povojnoveho-antisemitizmu-na-slovensku/ |title=Protizidovske nepokoje v Bratislave - August 1946 - August 1948. |accessdate=2017-02-26 |archive-date=2013-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623045108/http://www.druhasvetova.sk/2013/06/17/protizidovske-nepokoje-v-bratislave-august-1946-august-1948-v-atmosfere-povojnoveho-antisemitizmu-na-slovensku/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

1945年9月4-7日，在乌克兰的基辅，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quest-cdecjournal.it/focus.php?id=212|title=State-sponsored Anti-Semitism in Postwar USSR. Studies and Research Perspectives; Antonella Salomoni|accessdate=2012-07-26|date=|publisher=Quest. Issues in Contemporary Jewish History / Questioni di storia ebraica contemporanea|archive-date=2020-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122164317/http://www.quest-cdecjournal.it/focus.php?id=212|dead-url=no}}</ref>大约100多名犹太人遭打，其中36人被送往医院，5人不治身亡。<ref>Amir Weiner.</ref> 在俄罗斯的[[鲁布佐夫斯克|鲁布佐夫斯克]]，1945年也发生了多起反犹太人事件。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iO1u1qjs61IC&pg=RA1-PA228&lpg=RA1-PA228&dq=Rubtsovsk+1945&source=bl&ots=QJpvvo9cbm&sig=NDVN0PgNOOyPYu_Yge35rM2lmRc&hl=pl&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=2&ct=result#PRA1-PA229,M1|title=War, Holocaust and Stalinism: a ... - Google Książki|date=|publisher=Books.google.pl|accessdate=2010-04-08}}</ref>

